unittitle_ssm: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Printed Ephemera Collection on Individuals
abstract_ssm: The Tamiment Library, New York University, founded in 1906 as the library of the Rand School of Social Science, is a special collection documenting the history of United States radicalism, labor, and progressive social action. The Printed Ephemera Collection on Individuals consists of approximately 2,000 files containing flyers, broadsides, leaflets, clippings, reprints, reports, pamphlets, and other printed ephemera, arranged alphabetically.
